<h1>Online Bible: New World Translation of the Holy Scriptures</h1>
</noscript>
<p class="title">Esther 1:1-22</p>
<form class="formtext">
<input type="hidden" name="chapterCount" value="10">
<input type="hidden" name="verseCount" value="22">
<p><a name="bk1" class="vsAnchor">1</a>
       <span id="vs1">Now it came about in the days of A&middot;has&middot;u&middot;e&acute;rus, that is, the A&middot;has&middot;u&middot;e&acute;rus who was ruling as king from In&acute;di&middot;a to E&middot;thi&middot;o&acute;pi&middot;a, [over] a hundred and twenty-seven jurisdictional districts,</span> <a name="bk2" class="vsAnchor">2</a>
       <span id="vs2">[that] in those days as King A&middot;has&middot;u&middot;e&acute;rus was sitting upon his royal throne, which was in Shu&acute;shan the castle,</span> <a name="bk3" class="vsAnchor">3</a>
       <span id="vs3">in the third year of his reigning he held a banquet for all his princes and his servants, the military force of Persia and Me&acute;di&middot;a, the nobles and the princes of the jurisdictional districts before himself,</span> <a name="bk4" class="vsAnchor">4</a>
       <span id="vs4">when he showed the riches of his glorious kingdom and the honor [and] the beauty of his greatness for many days, a hundred and eighty days.</span> <a name="bk5" class="vsAnchor">5</a>
       <span id="vs5">And when these days had come to the full, the king held a banquet for seven days for all the people that were found in Shu&acute;shan the castle, for the great as well as the small, in the courtyard of the garden of the king’s palace.</span> <a name="bk6" class="vsAnchor">6</a>
       <span id="vs6">There were linen, fine cotton and blue held fast in ropes of fine fabric, and wool dyed reddish purple in silver rings and pillars of marble, couches of gold and silver upon a pavement of porphyry and marble and pearl and black marble.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk7" class="vsAnchor">7</a>
       <span id="vs7">And there was a passing of wine to drink in gold vessels; and the vessels were different from one another, and the royal wine was in great quantity, according to the means of the king.</span> <a name="bk8" class="vsAnchor">8</a>
       <span id="vs8">As regards the time of drinking according to the law, there was no one compelling, for that was the way the king had arranged for every great man of his household, to do according to the liking of each and every one.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk9" class="vsAnchor">9</a>
       <span id="vs9">Also, Vash&acute;ti the queen herself held a banquet for the women at the royal house that belonged to King A&middot;has&middot;u&middot;e&acute;rus.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk10" class="vsAnchor">10</a>
       <span id="vs10">On the seventh day, when the king’s heart was in a merry mood with wine, he said to Me&middot;hu&acute;man, Biz&acute;tha, Har&middot;bo&acute;na, Big&acute;tha and A&middot;bag&acute;tha, Ze&acute;thar and Car&acute;kas, the seven court officials that were ministering to the person of King A&middot;has&middot;u&middot;e&acute;rus,</span> <a name="bk11" class="vsAnchor">11</a>
       <span id="vs11">to bring Vash&acute;ti the queen in the royal headdress before the king, to show the peoples and the princes her loveliness; for she was beautiful in appearance.</span> <a name="bk12" class="vsAnchor">12</a>
       <span id="vs12">But Queen Vash&acute;ti kept refusing to come at the king’s word that was [conveyed] by means of the court officials. At this the king grew highly indignant and his very rage flared up within him.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk13" class="vsAnchor">13</a>
       <span id="vs13">And the king proceeded to say to the wise men having knowledge of the times (for in this way the king’s matter [came] before all those versed in law and legal cases,</span> <a name="bk14" class="vsAnchor">14</a>
       <span id="vs14">and those closest to him were Car&middot;she&acute;na, She&acute;thar, Ad&middot;ma&acute;tha, Tar&acute;shish, Me&acute;res, Mar&middot;se&acute;na, [and] Me&middot;mu&acute;can, seven princes of Persia and Me&acute;di&middot;a, having access to the king, [and] who were sitting first in the kingdom):</span> <a name="bk15" class="vsAnchor">15</a>
       <span id="vs15">“According to law what is to be done with Queen Vash&acute;ti because she has not performed the saying of King A&middot;has&middot;u&middot;e&acute;rus by means of the court officials?”</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk16" class="vsAnchor">16</a>
       <span id="vs16">To this Me&middot;mu&acute;can said before the king and the princes: “It is not against the king alone that Vash&acute;ti the queen has done wrong, but against all the princes and against all the peoples that are in all the jurisdictional districts of King A&middot;has&middot;u&middot;e&acute;rus.</span> <a name="bk17" class="vsAnchor">17</a>
       <span id="vs17">For the affair of the queen will go out to all the wives so that they will despise their owners in their own eyes, when they say, ‘King A&middot;has&middot;u&middot;e&acute;rus himself said to bring in Vash&acute;ti the queen before him, and she did not come in.’</span> <a name="bk18" class="vsAnchor">18</a>
       <span id="vs18">And this day the princesses of Persia and Me&acute;di&middot;a, who have heard the affair of the queen, will talk to all the princes of the king, and there will be plenty of contempt and indignation.</span> <a name="bk19" class="vsAnchor">19</a>
       <span id="vs19">If to the king it does seem good, let a royal word go out from his person, and let it be written among the laws of Persia and Me&acute;di&middot;a, that it may not pass away, that Vash&acute;ti may not come in before King A&middot;has&middot;u&middot;e&acute;rus; and her royal dignity let the king give to a companion of hers, a woman better than she is.</span> <a name="bk20" class="vsAnchor">20</a>
       <span id="vs20">And the decree of the king that he will make must be heard in all his realm (for it is vast), and all the wives themselves will give honor to their owners, the great as well as the small.”</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk21" class="vsAnchor">21</a>
       <span id="vs21">And the thing was pleasing in the eyes of the king and the princes, and the king proceeded to do according to the word of Me&middot;mu&acute;can.</span> <a name="bk22" class="vsAnchor">22</a>
       <span id="vs22">So he sent written documents to all the king’s jurisdictional districts, to each jurisdictional district in its own style of writing and to each people in its own tongue, for every husband to be continually acting as prince in his own house and speaking in the tongue of his own people.</span>
</p>
</form>

<script language="JavaScript1.2" type="text/javascript">
