<h1>Online Bible: New World Translation of the Holy Scriptures</h1>
</noscript>
<p class="title">Esther 7:1-10</p>
<form class="formtext">
<input type="hidden" name="chapterCount" value="10">
<input type="hidden" name="verseCount" value="10">
<p><a name="bk1" class="vsAnchor">1</a>
       <span id="vs1">Then the king and Ha&acute;man came in to banquet with Esther the queen.</span> <a name="bk2" class="vsAnchor">2</a>
       <span id="vs2">The king now said to Esther also on the second day during the banquet of wine: “What is your petition, O Esther the queen? Let it even be given to you. And what is your request? To the half of the kingship—let it even be done!”</span> <a name="bk3" class="vsAnchor">3</a>
       <span id="vs3">At this Esther the queen answered and said: “If I have found favor in your eyes, O king, and if to the king it does seem good, let there be given me my own soul at my petition and my people at my request.</span> <a name="bk4" class="vsAnchor">4</a>
       <span id="vs4">For we have been sold, I and my people, to be annihilated, killed and destroyed. Now if we had been sold for mere men slaves and for mere maidservants, I should have kept silent. But the distress is not appropriate when with damage to the king.”</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk5" class="vsAnchor">5</a>
       <span id="vs5">King A&middot;has&middot;u&middot;e&acute;rus now said, yes, he went on to say to Esther the queen: “Who is this, and just where is the one who has emboldened himself to do that way?”</span> <a name="bk6" class="vsAnchor">6</a>
       <span id="vs6">Then Esther said: “The man, the adversary and enemy, is this bad Ha&acute;man.”</span>
</p>

<p> 
       <span id="vs6-2">As for Ha&acute;man, he became terrified because of the king and the queen.</span> <a name="bk7" class="vsAnchor">7</a>
       <span id="vs7">As for the king, he rose up in his rage from the banquet of wine [to go] to the garden of the palace; and Ha&acute;man himself stood up to make request for his soul from Esther the queen, for he saw that bad had been determined against him by the king.</span> <a name="bk8" class="vsAnchor">8</a>
       <span id="vs8">And the king himself returned from the garden of the palace to the house of the wine banquet; and Ha&acute;man was fallen upon the couch on which Esther was. Consequently the king said: “Is there also to be a raping of the queen, with me in the house?” The word itself went out of the king’s mouth, and Ha&acute;man’s face they covered.</span> <a name="bk9" class="vsAnchor">9</a>
       <span id="vs9">Har&middot;bo&acute;na, one of the court officials before the king, now said: “Also, there is the stake that Ha&acute;man made for Mor&acute;de&middot;cai, who had spoken good concerning the king, standing in Ha&acute;man’s house—fifty cubits high.” At that the king said: “Y<span class="smallcaps">OU</span> men, hang him on it.”</span> <a name="bk10" class="vsAnchor">10</a>
       <span id="vs10">And they proceeded to hang Ha&acute;man on the stake that he had prepared for Mor&acute;de&middot;cai; and the king’s rage itself subsided.</span>
</p>
</form>

