<h1>Online Bible: New World Translation of the Holy Scriptures</h1>
</noscript>
<p class="title">Esther 10:1-3</p>
<form class="formtext">
<input type="hidden" name="chapterCount" value="10">
<input type="hidden" name="verseCount" value="3">
<p><a name="bk1" class="vsAnchor">1</a>
       <span id="vs1">And King A&middot;has&middot;u&middot;e&acute;rus proceeded to lay forced labor upon the land and the isles of the sea.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk2" class="vsAnchor">2</a>
       <span id="vs2">As for all his energetic work and his mightiness and the exact statement of Mor&acute;de&middot;cai’s greatness with which the king magnified him, are they not written in the Book of the affairs of the times of the kings of Me&acute;di&middot;a and Persia?</span> <a name="bk3" class="vsAnchor">3</a>
       <span id="vs3">For Mor&acute;de&middot;cai the Jew was second to King A&middot;has&middot;u&middot;e&acute;rus and was great among the Jews and approved by the multitude of his brothers, working for the good of his people and speaking peace to all their offspring.</span>
</p>
</form>

